[{"id":"VR857477","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal mirrors in parallel to each other. An incident light ray originating from the upper left of the image travels downward and to the right towards the bottom mirror. The incident ray strikes the mirror about one fourth of the way along the bottom mirror.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857477.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A ray of light is directed at an angle between two parallel, horizontal mirrors, as shown in the figure. Which of the following ray diagrams correctly depicts the path of the ray as it gets reflected from the two mirrors? For answers C and D, in which the ray is shown retracing its path, the numbers indicate the order in which rays are reflected.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857477_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal mirrors in parallel to each other. An incident light ray originates from the upper left of the figure and travels downward and to right towards the bottom mirror. The incident ray strikes the mirror about one fourth of the way along the bottom mirror. The light ray is reflected upwards and to the right, reaching the top mirror about three fourths of the way. The light ray then is reflected again downward and to the right traveling past the right edge of the bottom mirror.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857477.g02.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal mirrors in parallel to each other. An incident light ray originates from the upper left of the image and travels downward and to right. The light ray strikes the bottom mirror about one fourth of the way along the bottom mirror. The light ray then reflects upward and to the right, reaching the top mirror about three fourths of the way. The light ray then reflects straight down perpendicular to the bottom mirror. The light ray then reflects again traveling upward and to the left, reaching the top mirror about a fourth of the way from the left. Finally, the light ray reflects downward and to the left traveling past the left edge of the bottom mirror.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857477.g03.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal mirrors in parallel to each other. Four paths taken by the light ray are numbered 1 through 4. In path 1 the light ray originates from the upper left of the figure and travels towards the bottom mirror striking it about one fourth of the way along the bottom mirror. Then, in path 2, it reflects straight up striking the upper mirror perpendicularly. In path 3 it reflects off the top mirror straight down to the bottom mirror. In path 4 it reflects upward and to the left from the bottom mirror, following the same path as in the initial path 1.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857477.g04.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal mirrors in parallel to each other. A light ray takes seven paths numbered 1 through 7. In path 1, the light ray originates from the upper left of the figure and travels to the bottom mirror striking it about one fourth of the way along the bottom mirror. Then, in path 2, it reflects straight up to the upper mirror. In path 3 it reflects straight down to the bottom mirror. Paths 4, 5, 6, 7 indicate subsequent reflections perpendicular to both mirrors. An ellipse next to the representation of paths 2, 4 and 6 and paths 3, 5 and 7 suggests that the pattern continues.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857477.g05.svg\"/></span></p>"],"answer":0}]